caption: This is an excellent little restaurant. I made reservations beforehand easily on the website, service was prompt and the space was small but not cramped. Would definitely recommend more for dates than large groups.  The food was phenomenal. We got the Samosas as an appetizer and they were very tasty, a little spicy, and hot. My Dutch burger was cooked right, juicy, tender, and flavorful. The Gnocchi with Crab was also good, as I got to sneak a bite from my date. For dessert, the lemon poppy seed cake was very flavorful and well balanced. A nice little elegant dessert.  The homemade elements of each course were addressed by our waiter, who I believe was also the owner. I could really feel the love put into the recipes.  Drinks were good too, nothing too crazy complicated, but done right.  One of the best dining experiences I’ve had in Iowa City!

We had pasta. I had the mushroom pasta with chicken and my date had the shrimp linguine. We had chicken fingers and samosas for our appetizers. The food was delicious, fragrant, and the chicken was organic. And the chocolate truffle was amazing. Also, the owner was so attentive and nice. We will definitely come back.

Had a lovely experience, service was very accommodating and polite. The bacon croquettas and the vegetable samosas were amazing. As well as the burgers, the 126 burger was amazing quality and had great taste for a very reasonable price.
Looking for a place to dine in and found this one.  Excellent food!  Everything is made in house, just delicious!  I recommend this place to anyone.
Food was fantastic, in house made sauce on the tuna was amazing. Small drink selection
Very good food and service absolutely wonderful place definitely check it out

This place is SOOOOO good! They have great vegan and gluten-free options!! It’s also celiac friendly! The owner was so nice and helpful. We all felt so welcomed and taken care of. Basically, everything is house made! We will definitely be back!
The 126 is a wonderful dining experience, consistently.  Food and service and atmosphere are all a win!
Cute, intimate, and cozy place. Service was great and there is a good menu.
One of my favorite restaurants!
Very very good food! Relaxed environment, too!

Our service was absolutely incredible. Our server, Matthew, was very kind and helpful to what was on the menu. The food was great and wonderfully cooked. The inside is on the smaller side but is warm and cozy all at the same time. I would recommend this place to anyone visiting Iowa City. We had one of the best meals of the year here.
Incredible food, nice atmosphere, great service. Highly recommend the lamb and vegan curry entrees on the dinner menu.

You have to eat here.126 has always been a hidden Iowa City gem for me, my whole life. Their local farm to table menu, passionate owners & staff shine through their food. I love grabbing lunch here by myself, especially during patio season. I've celebrated New Years Eve, with an amazing tasting menu. I've also attended extremely small and intimate weddings, in this beautiful space.  Understand that eating here, with the open kitchen and lovely exposed brick makes you feel part of the community and is right for pretty much any occasion.

Really high quality food. Their produce is top notch. Best salads in Iowa city. The samosas were made in-house and really delicious. A tad on the pricey side, but well worth it. This is among the best and freshest food I've had in Iowa City.
I recommend the lamb
Great food & atmosphere. Good for formal meetings as well
Great food and the owner has a wonderful personality and a impeccable memory for his customers. A must try if you're in the Iowa City area

You guys! This place is just delightful. We first ate here around 15 years ago for a residency interview dinner and it’s been on our list of places to return to ever since. The menu now is more eclectic and interesting and includes several vegetarian and vegan options which is really cool. The owner Matthew is so passionate about his product and the care he puts in is evident. Kudos to him for soldiering on despite the COVID pandemic. This is a difficult time for fine dining establishments but he maintains an excellent experience. We had drinks including the mojito and gin rickey and they were incredible....fresh and sweet and tart—just right. We had the vegetable samosas, made fresh in house and omg delightful! The mint chutney was amazing. All four in our party loved our entrees but the winners were the 126 burger (with house ground local beef and homemade brioche bun) and the ancho rubbed pork chop (tender and full of flavor with amazing Brussels sprouts on the side—absolutely delicious). We ended with homemade sorbet and poppyseed cake and they were a perfect light ending to a delicious meal. To top it all off we had amazing, prompt, attentive service.  I think this little place is a treasure and a labor of love, and a visit will be well worth your time. Please support local fine dining establishments here and wherever your home town is...we don’t want to lose the chance to sit and visit and take delight in amazing food like what is being offered over at one twenty six!
Delicious food and wonderful service! Can't wait for our next visit.

My daughter and son in law are in Iowa City for Residency at the U. We stumbled on this place for a patio lunch the first weekend in town. Had a craving on a recent visit and Matthew, the owner, remembered us! I had forgotten how amazing the house-made hand cut fries are and of three different burgers we ordered, each thought it was the best we'd EVER had. The craft cocktails were excellent. Matthew even put together kids meals for our 2 and 4 year olds. Thoroughly enjoyable evening on a shady patio downtown. My SIL said he's never eating anywhere else in Iowa City.   Highly recommend! Covid-safe contact free pick up and great outdoor space.

the stake frites was disappointing, the texture was more like rare then medium rare, but that's it, nothing else was added. the stake supposed to be  with porcini or gorgonzola butter, but it just tasted like garlic and char with a big pile of french fries and an ounce of ketchup. all of this for 28 bucks. was not bad but was not good either, thank you never again.

Had the worst service ever. The waitress name was Amos, she was rude and unhelpful. She failed to mention that gratuity was already include on the bill, so we tremendously over tipped. I will never be back.  There are other better options for fine dinning in the downtown area. I think Basta, Baroncini’s, Pullman’s, and Orchard Green are exponentially better in terms of food and service.

great place for a date night.

Made our reservation through Open Table after careful consideration of the many choices in Iowa City and Coralville. This was our "nice" dinner while at the University Of Iowa attending continuing education classes.  I lived here for 11 years nearly 30 years ago, return every few years to attend class to maintain my dental license. Reservation was for 6:15 on Friday the 11th of October on a football weekend.  Arrived at 6:10, seated right away.  Water was brought and drinks were ordered.  Drinks served, and appetizers ordered, a cheese plate with three very good cheeses, dates, walnuts and perfectly toasted French bread.  We also had the marinated olives which complimented the cheeses very well. Order another glass of wine and dinner.  Wife ordered the steak frites medium and I the tenderloin medium it was complimented with whipped potatoes and broccolini.  Or I should say I think it was.  Original entree order was placed at approximately 6:30-6:35 also ordered the bread basket (it's not complementary) bread came just a few minutes later.  At 7:20 our young lady server brings two simple dinner salads explaining that another server had inexplicably taken our order to another table.  Please accept these salads and of course the wine is also on us. Salads, simply greens with a nice vinaigrette.  No bread left but that's fine.  The trek to the bathrooms go directly by open kitchen up a long flight of stairs. After the salads went to the bathroom up the very tall stairs for the second time we've been here nearly 1 1/2 hours with cheese and bread and wine........ coming down the stairs there is NOTHING on the grill? Get to the table there is still no food. It's almost 8:00pm.  Olives, bread, drinks (the cocktail not the wine she said was comped) cheese.  We decided to put $40 cash on the table and left.   We did briefly say we had to leave, to our waitress as she stood running another patrons tab. We told her we had left some $ on the table and she just smiles and says oh really?  Then we went to find food.  I would have thought when our order was found to be lost every effort to bring our dishes as quickly as possible would have been afforded.  Or at the very least kept updated. Nothing no communication after the salads were given.  We ended up at 8:15 pm trying to find a place to eat on a football weekend in Iowa City.  So disappointed.
Great vibe. Great service. Best burger in Iowa city.
A hidden gem in downtown Iowa City. Amazing food, attentive staff and management.

If you love good food you must visit Moonrakers. Pulled pork Cuban is out of this world, maybe the Moon. I love my soup very hot, and without asking, that is how it came out. I will absolutely be back. Nicely done

This is billed as an upscale French restaurant. I don’t know if we caught them on an off night or what. The lamb was passable but I didn’t like the watery texture of the polenta. My husband had the hanger steak which was way overpriced for chewy meat and a huge plate of French fries. The desserts were delicious. They have an extensive wine selection and a full bar but no cocktail menu.

No wifi for a working lunch but if all you need is food & wine, this is an excellent choice.  I had the fries as an appetizer and a bacon cheeseburger that comes with a simple and tasty salad.

This place was really "different". The outside of the building looked old & worn down, and the inside didn't look much different. As I entered the dungeon, I felt as if I was in an alley between two really high ancient brick buildings cause that's what the walls of this place were: just solid raw brick, no paint, dark, simple wood tables, no decorations of any kind. A very tall, slender, guy approached me. He greeted me. I asked him for a menu. He explained they were no longer serving their lunch specials and that I was there at kind of an odd time. I told him that I just wanted something that "tasted good" that was "filling". He said, "I got just the thing for you. It's a sandwich we make called Cuban Pork". I said, "I'll take it". He said, "Would you like any fries with it?" I said, "Yes". He asked me where I'd like to sit and suggested that it would be nice to sit outside cause it was a nice day. I smiled and said that I'd rather sit next to the open window. He grinned broadly and said wherever you'd like. He didn't ask me if I'd like anything to drink, but said he'd bring water. I hate water, but I didn't say anything. He brought the water. It was in a nice large very clean looking glass. I took a sip half expecting to taste chemicals (city water). I didn't. I actually liked the water. He brought my food. I don't really like pork too well, but if someone says something is good, I just get it. The Cuban Pork was so awesome that it was out of this world. Wow, I thought. I wasn't too impressed by the fries, but I'm not really a frie person anyway. You'll just have to try them yourself. The fries came with ketchup, but I hate ketchup, so I asked if they had any hot sauce. He said they had Sriracha. I said that's even better. The meal was a good portion of food and it costed under $15. I was real impressed by my waiter though. He was a very nice guy with a very friendly smile. Another guy from the back even said hi and gave me a wave. They make you feel like you're home at this place, so I gave him a $3 tip for the hospitality, and the really awesome sandwich. You're probably thinking, "Then why not 5-stars?" Cause I wasn't crazy about the fries. Poor excuse, I know, but I'm very very picky about what I eat. I highly recommend this place though. All my 4-star and 5-star reviews are worthy places. Stars are just what my personal experience was, but yours may be better. Not everyone is going to have the same experience. Try this place out today.

Although the waiter was attentive, it took an hour and 15 minutes for our food to arrive. I saw some people leave because they didn't want to wait so long. The food was decent, but expensive. Lunch for one person cost $25.20. This price was for an open-faced chicken sandwich, salad, and iced tea. A 20% tip was automatically added. I noticed that the alcoholic drink menu is also very expensive, with a glass of beer $7 on up. You must climb steep stairs to get to the dining area.

I’ve never had such an outrageous dining experience in my life.  Mistakes happen at restaurants, and I’m understanding when food takes an extra long time or you deliver the wrong food.  When my girlfriend and I were at Moonrakers, one of our plates had been delivered to another man first who began eating from it.  When he realized his order was wrong, that exact plate with his used condiments was delivered to me.  This is beyond a simple mistake, and dangerous if it’s not also a violation of health code.  No amount of being busy makes this a reasonable or acceptable way to do business.  Now I’m wondering if my girlfriend is sick because Moonrakers gave her the fries that someone else had started eating already.  They didn’t acknowledge that our food had already been picked at until we said something, and then we got to wait another 45 minutes on top of our long original long wait for food.  I have to advise steering clear of a place that’s so wantonly reckless with their approach to their customers’ health.

In from out of town for work alone. Wanted mussels and a cheese plate. Found One Twenty Six from Google and so happy I did. Very cute, quaint restaurant. Food was delicious, staff was on point and I'm extremely satisfied! Definitely recommend. Parking was a pain but that is not the restaurant s fault. Try it for sure for a small, local spot!!!!

Ate here with a big group on a Thursday night with a pre-fix menu. The service was excellent, and they had an extensive wine list (I picked a cote du rhone which was good). They brought out several appetizer pizzas (margherita and bacon-onion) which were crispy and delicious. The salad was a good mix of field greens (no cheap iceberg) and, while listed to come with balsamic vinaigrette, came with a surprisingly good and slightly spicy tomatillo dressing. They brought out plates of fries for tables to share, which were fresh and crisp. For the main course, I got the local grass fed burger with bacon. The meat was probably the best on a hamburger I've had in ages, and came medium rare, as requested. The bun was good, but they slathered mayonnaise on the top half (not indicated by the menu) so the top half was left to waste. I had the chocolate torte-like desert with raspberry sauce, which was rich and delicious. Only complaint I can come up with was the mayo on the bun.
Food portions are small, cocktails were weak, service was decent. Overall very underwhelmed. Cute atmosphere. Expected more.

I got lunch to go today and it was quite possibly the most wonderful thing I've ever put in my mouth.  I got the County Salad, which you would think is just a salad but it was heavenly!  The shrimp was cooked perfectly and the flavors just melted together.  The grape (or cherry) tomatoes are the tastiest I've ever had!  They took something simple and made it phenomenal!  I will definitely be frequenting this establishment!
The pizza here is amazing! The crust was perfect and i probably ate it all in about 2 minutes. Feel of the restaurant is great and i will definitely be going back!

ok once you wait 10 minutes for pretentious staff to actually show up at table. Pass on artichoke salad, must be a epic shortage of dressing because salad is drier than my time in Iraq. We were very disappointed with our experience at Moonrakers. The place was empty when our party of two arrived for dinner at about 6pm on December 26th. The chardonnay we received was flat, obviously from a bottle that had been open for a while. We ordered a burger and curry wrap, both with fries which were limp as soon as we received them. The burger was fine (it's hard to botch organic beef on a house-made bun) but oversalted. The curry wrap, however, was essentially Spanish rice in a tortilla, lacking heavily in curry and virtually absent of vegetables (if there were any, perhaps they were minced and included in the tomato sauce). Simply put, it was not a proper curry and very disappointing.  The place has a nice look overall, but this is hampered by glaring lights, muted big screen TVs, and high volume coming from the bar TV.  Our service was efficient but cold. The menu specifically states that burgers are prepared as per the customer's request, but I wasn't asked how I wanted my burger.  One could easily find a random establishment that provides better bar food than what we received here, or at least know to deliver crisp fries. Having both worked in food service, we know what we received was unacceptable.  The bottom line: The quality didn't live up to the prices. We would never go there again, or bother to try Hearth or One Twenty Six, which are at a higher price range.
